#X text 12 8 2 Introduction to Gem - gemchains;
#X text 17 67 Gem Chains represent visual entities (things you can
see in the gem window) in gem. For example a single square is defined
by a gemchain inside of PD. These gemchains always begin (at the top)
with "gemhead" and always end (at the bottom) with geometry objects
(for example circle \, square \, cube etc..). Between the gemhead and
the geometry are the objects that change the entity's attributes. Here
is a simple gem chain that defines a blue square. The Toggle connected
to the gemhead tells PD whether it should render the square: "1" or
not: "0". This way you can turn entities on and off in your scene without
deleting and re-creating gemchains.;
